Ecology and geographical distribution.
Glyptoxanthus erosus
has been reported from the Atlantic coast of the United States (North Carolina to Florida), from the Gulf of Mexico , the Bahamas , the Yucatan Peninsula, and from the Caribbean Sea (see
Rathbun 1930
;
Guinot 1979
;
Williams 1984
).
G. erosus
has generally been collected subtidally from sandy to rocky and coralline bottoms to a maximum depth of 90 m (see
Williams 1984
).
